name: Ace Bushy 'Outside It's Cold' T-Shirt
description:
We've a new album coming out later this year.

The record has been titled and we thought we'd start the promotional push with a new t-shirt design. It looks really snazzy we think! It was designed by Sarah Graley/Growley and Greg Bird. They did great jobs!

It's been printed white and black on a light blue t-shirt so that's why it costs a little more than out previous t-shirts, soz! We're selling it at just over cost price so yr getting a mega deal for sure!

So yeah, order the t-shirt and we'll send it to you dead quick. If you live in Brum/know us then we'll refund yr postage as we can give it to you irl ok.

Oh and you can see them being made by the fantastic Get A Grip guys online - http://getagripstudio.tumblr.com/post/21260940412/possibly-my-favorite-print-so-far-this-year-black

ILU x

name: Daniel Ershov Has Been Offered £100,000 By An Eccentric Millionaire...
description:
Daniel Ershov Has Been Offered £100,000 By An Eccentric Millionaire To Step Naked From A Car Onto A Busy City Street, Walk 200 Meters And Climb Back Into The Car

Our second album, recorded between July and October 2009 was released in November but we've only just had it printed up on cd. It is a really good record full of brilliant songs.

It's been printed on a digipack and it looks really sweet. It also has a lyric sheet blutacked to the inside so you can learn the words to sing along if you want!

Tracklisting

  1. Whirlwind Regulations
  2. It’s Impossible 2 Keep The Love Strong When Yr Such Different Shapes (2.5D)
  3. Iluvya (Hate Version)
  4. Brown Eyes Be Careful
  5. Anna Log Is In Mild Peril (Because Of The Sea Etch)
  6. Iluvya Pts. Two & Three
  7. James and James and James and James
  8. Yrjustaflower

name: Split Cassette with Saints Innocents
description:
Split Cassette with Saints Innocents

Split cassette with Oxford thrashcore good guys, Saints Innocents. Released by/on Les Editions De Minuit, July 2009. It's pretty much like going to a 363 house party but you can listen in yr bedroom instead of going all the way to Oxford.

All proceeds from this release go to help punk rockers in Oxford (basically we'll give it to the Editions guys because they put this out and are the best people ever).

Side A (Saints Innocents)

  1. Zombie 3
  2. There Goes Michigan
  3. Bottled Violence (Minor Threat Cover)

Side B (Ace Bushy Striptease)

  1. Weave Away To Make Stars
  2. Totally Ice Cream
